Why choose between doing meaningful work and having a fulfilling life? At MITRE, you can have both. That's because MITRE people are committed to tackling our nation's toughest challenges‚Äîand we're committed to the long-term well-being of our employees. MITRE is different from most technology companies. We are a not-for-profit corporation chartered to work for the public interest, with no... commercial conflicts to influence what we do. The R&D centers we operate for the government create lasting impact in fields as diverse as cybersecurity, healthcare, aviation, defense, and enterprise transformation. We're making a difference every day‚Äîworking for a safer, healthier, and more secure nation and world. Our workplace reflects our values. We offer competitive benefits, exceptional professional development opportunities, and a culture of innovation that embraces diversity, inclusion, flexibility, collaboration, and career growth. If this sounds like the choice you want to make, then choose MITRE‚Äîand make a difference with us.

The Enabling Technology Department (N411), part of the Collection and Tasking Division within the MITRE Intelligence Center, applies broad Defense, Intelligence, and Federal Law Enforcement expertise, and a deep understanding of operational tradecraft as well as our sponsors' intelligence collection challenges, to develop and advance innovative human and technical solutions which enable present and future multi-int collection management from tactical to enterprise levels, and to shape and grow the future MITRE intelligence workforce through intentional talent development. Whether enabling technology for customer- or discipline-specific systems, better integration of National and theater collection, fully orchestrated all-discipline, all-domain collection, or enabling career excellence for intelligence professionals, we are ready to engage with the complex intelligence collection challenges facing our nation.

Job Responsibilities :

The Department is currently seeking an early-mid career multi-disciplinary intelligence professional to contribute broad individual technical expertise and support to a diverse and growing work program supporting multiple Intelligence Community sponsors and missions. The successful candidate will thrive by delivering technical and professional expertise contributing to the solution of hard problems, teaming, leading and developing others, and applying mature knowledge, skills, and mission application experience in at least some of the following areas: intelligence/counterintelligence collection/analysis; independent evaluation and assessment; strategic analysis of cost, schedule, quality, and risk variables to enable effective performance management; oversight/integration of technology development and engineering efforts; and/or operational/mission analysis to support executive decision making. The ideal candidate will not only serve as an exemplary individual contributor developing and delivering high-impact outcomes but will also contribute to development of future plans for a range of sponsor-facing projects focused in areas including intelligence collection capability development, technical evaluation, and SME/trusted advisor partner engagements across sponsor work programs. This position will represent MITRE to senior government stakeholders and will contribute to MITRE‚Äôs trusted relationships with their organizations in support of frequently shifting mission priorities. The position will be primarily centered on the McLean campus, with CONUS travel expected 5-10%.

Key Responsibilities/Work Breakdown:

As a member of a high-performance MITRE team, work closely and collaboratively with a diverse group of partners (government, FFRDC, and possibly commercial vendors, including operators/users, systems and software engineers, government program managers, and analysts) to:
‚Ä¢ Evaluate existing methodologies and develop recommendations for improved processes, tools, analytics, and infrastructure;
‚Ä¢ Review proposed ideas and conduct rigorous analyses to determine feasibility and guide effective implementation planning;
‚Ä¢ Survey, evaluate, and prioritize emerging technologies for alignments to strategic mission gaps;
‚Ä¢ Identify and leverage capabilities from across MITRE that enable the Sponsor to measurably increase mission impact;
‚Ä¢ Support intelligence collection operations by partnering closely with Sponsor leaders to apply human and technological capabilities that enable successful operational/mission outcomes;
‚Ä¢ Convey technical, analytic, and organizational findings, recommendations, and approaches to senior executive decision makers.

Minimum Qualifications:

Applicants selected for this position will be subject to a government security investigation and must meet eligibility requirements for access to classified information or applicants who are eligible for security clearances.

Required Qualifications :
‚Ä¢ Current/active TS/SCI clearance;
‚Ä¢ Education: BS or equivalent (Systems Engineering or relevant national security field);
‚Ä¢ Ability/willingness to work full time onsite in classified US government facilities;
‚Ä¢ Demonstrated success in providing sponsors/mission partners with the data, analysis, strategies, and implementation support required to address critical issues, setting and meeting strategic objectives, and advancing short and long-term program goals;
‚Ä¢ Skills and commitment to building and sustaining high-performance teams, achieving team goals, growing trust, and collaboration;
‚Ä¢ Must be a self-starter with creative thinking and problem-solving capabilities, able to function within an ambiguous and dynamic environment with minimal supervision;
‚Ä¢ Broad and diverse background in different technical and/or analysis roles, ranging from individual contributions to project / program leadership on complex projects;
‚Ä¢ Excellent communication effectiveness, both written and verbal;
‚Ä¢ Demonstrated effectiveness in interacting with technical staff, analysts, and operators ranging from junior-level contributors to the most senior leaders (GO/SES/SIS) in the government;
‚Ä¢ Minimum 7+ years of experience in diverse US Defense/National Security technical or human intelligence domain roles;
‚Ä¢ Thorough understanding of mission application of intelligence/counterintelligence collection tradecraft, systems, processes and governance;
‚Ä¢ Experience with intelligence-supporting processes and strategies (e.g. enterprise capabilities, intelligence cycle or application of intelligence principles to solve unique problems).

Preferred Qualifications :
‚Ä¢ Education: Graduate degree (MA/MS or equivalent);
‚Ä¢ Experience in a consulting role, advising executive government leaders, and demonstrating the highest degree of professional and diplomatic skills in advocating technology and program directions;
‚Ä¢ Intelligence community acquisition, planning, programming, budgeting and execution experience;
‚Ä¢ Recognized as a thought leader by MITRE/sponsor leadership;
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with broad intelligence community organizational and governance structures, policy generation processes, life cycle acquisition processes, and/or requirements processes.

